    n = len(probs)
    dp = [0] * (n + 1)
    dp[0] = 1

        state = 0
        for j in range(i + 1):
          #print(state, p, 1-p, dp[j])
          curr = dp[j]
          dp[j] = (curr * (1 - p)) + state
          state =  curr * p

    return sum(dp[(n + 1) // 2:])

p = 10 ** 9 + 7

def modpow(a, n, MOD):
  res = 1
  while (n > 0):
    if (n & 1):
      res = res * a % MOD
    a = a * a % MOD
    n >>= 1
  return res

def cmb(n, r, p):
  A = 1
  for i in range(r):
    A *= (n - i)
    A *= modpow(i + 1, p - 2, p)
    A %= p
  return A

    y = np.arange(1, UP, dtype=np.int64)
    den = N * x * y
    num = 4*x*y - N*y - N*x
    y = y[(den % num == 0) & (num > 0)]

                nums[i-1], nums[i] = nums[i], nums[i-1]
